  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Swim Coach",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>We are an Austswim Gold accredited swim school offering lessons from 4 months old to adults catering to all levels from water familiarisation, learn to swim lessons focused on technique and competitive squads.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Marsden Swim School seeks passionate swimming instructors (Or passionate people, qualification can be provided) to deliver safe, engaging lessons for babies, children, and adults, following a structured curriculum and fostering confidence and skill development.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct engaging and safe swimming lessons for babies, children, and adults across various skill levels, following Marsden Swim School’s structured curriculum and safety protocols</li><li>Provide clear, regular progress feedback to students and parents through the customer portal to support learning and improvement</li><li>Manage and coordinate class schedules, communicating effectively with the operations team to ensure smooth lesson delivery</li><li>Create and maintain a positive, inclusive, and encouraging learning environment that supports student confidence and skill growth</li><li>Demonstrate professionalism and punctuality in all coaching duties and interactions</li><li>Participate in in-house training to develop coaching skills and knowledge</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Passion for teaching and working with children and adults in a swim school environment</li><li>Ability to lead classes independently or with support, showing confidence and reliability</li><li>Effective communication skills in English to engage students, parents, and team members</li><li>Flexibility to work weekday afternoons and weekends as scheduling requires</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills and a genuine interest in teaching swimming as a life skill</li><li>Austswim certification can be provided by us</li></ul><p><br />Pay flexible at $40-$50 per hour (Generally shifts are between 2 - 4 hours, on weekends can do 2 shifts in a day)</p>",
